<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="279" type="vernacular_names">(TRUE HAMSTERS, VOLES, LEMMINGS AND NEW WORLD RATS AND MICE)</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="279" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1259,2140,861,1012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• Very small to medium-large rodents, rarely large, mostly with generalized cursorial body plans and typically not sexually dimorphic.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707178" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707178" box="[1259,1448,979,1012]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707178/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="279" startId="0.[1259,1272,979,1012]" targetBox="[1472,2016,1026,1218]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1259,2140,861,1012]" box="[1259,1448,979,1012]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• 10-70 cm.</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707182" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707182/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="279" startId="0.[1259,1272,1255,1288]" targetBox="[245,1190,864,1487]" targetPageId="0">
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2141,1255,1493]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• Holarctic and Neotropical regions, marginally into Indo-Malayan Region.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2141,1255,1493]" box="[1259,2041,1334,1367]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• Virtually all terrestrial and some aquatic habitats.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2141,1255,1493]" box="[1258,2045,1374,1407]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• 142 genera, 765 species, at least 1505 extant taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[1258,2141,1255,1493]" pageId="0" pageNumber="279">• 20 species Critically Endangered, 32 species Endangered, 40 species Vulnerable; 15 species Extinct since 1600.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
